# Git for Mac OS

check OS git version

```bash
$ git --version
```

where Git is installed

```bash
$ which git
```

if output is `/usr/bin` run the following

```bash
$ export PATH=/usr/local/bin:$PATH
$ # now should look like this `/usr/local/bin/git`
```

install git via homebrew

```  
$ brew install git
```

update git

```
$ brew upgrade git
```
